M December 13, 1909.

Mr. Paul Moore Strayer, Pastor,
The Third Presbyterian Church,
Rochester, N. Y.

Dear Sir:

In the absence of President Gompers I beg to acknowledge receipt of your favor of December 10, and to say that same will be brought to Mr. Gompers' attention at the earliest opportunity.

Very truly yours,

Sec. to President Gompers.
",
    "summary": "The letter, dated December 13, 1909, acknowledges the receipt of a correspondence from December 10 and assures that it will be brought to the attention of President Gompers at the earliest opportunity. It is addressed to Pastor Paul Moore Strayer of The Third Presbyterian Church in Rochester, New York.",
